reviews_data.review_text: I like this location. It seems their recipes are very consistent and it doesn’t depend on who is working. The teas taste great. I have tried other locations like the one on south blvd and that one always disappoints me. Their tea taste weird and it’s never consistent. Sometimes is too watery and not creamy, sometimes the bobas are too hard or bland etc. this fort mill locations seems to always have the tea taste very consistent and yummy. Definitely recommend this fort mill location.

One of the worst boba places I’ve had. You’re better off just flushing 15 dollars down the toilet. The rose hip milk tea tasted like raspberry instead of rose and the cocoa wow was basically just straight milk. The rose tasted so strongly of  raspberry syrup I could not finish it. I only got normal sweetness and a milk cap in which you would think would cut the amount of syrup in the drink. My fiancé says it tasted almost burnt. Boba could’ve been cooked better as it was very chewy but still edible. The kung fu tea in Columbia tasted much better but they got rid of the creme brûlée matcha. :( cashier was nice.

I came by Kung Fu Tea over the past year and have loved every visit! Staff are very polite and the flavors I get are very exotic and tasty. From brewed coffees, to fruity or milky tea, the choice is yours. They also have unique cups showing the different themes and events like Minions, Super Mario and more. I think it's worth checking out for those who like bubble tea. 😊
The tea was soooo yummy and the interior is sooo inviting and the workers were very sweet :)

I ordered a tea with tapioca boba, but the boba wasn’t cooked thoroughly all the way and it was hard in the middle. This was disappointing when this was a special treat for myself and the boba was practically uncooked. However workers were very nice
Would come again.

This location has terrible customer service. Every time there's a loyalty event, they shut down or disable the online app to keep customers from getting special deals. It's like they don't care about rewarding loyalty at all. If they don't want to support their loyal customers, why should we support them? This behavior is unacceptable, and I'm done giving them my business.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi S, we understand your frustration, and we hope you’ll understand our side as well. The only time we turn off online orders is when we receive such an overwhelming volume of orders at once that we have to use it as a last resort to make operations more manageable, like we had to do earlier tonight. We have to prioritize the accuracy and quality of our orders, and sometimes that means limiting the number of new orders for a time. It isn’t to bar customers from earning rewards, but to help our baristas get orders out at a more reasonable pace.

reviews_data.review_text: Oh my god I feel like I just drank from the fountain of youth. this drink has cured my depression, cleaned my house, watered my crops. I have ascended to the afterlife and god has greeted me personally.
I would suggest offering soy, almond, or oat milk for those who are lactose intolerant or food allergies. Coffee places offer this we why can't Boba Tea houses?
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi Evelyn! So all of our milk teas use a non-dairy milk powder, and anything else that uses milk in it is made with lactose-free Lactaid milk. We also have several options that don’t use any milk powder or Lactaid milk, such as fruit punches and classic teas. As a franchise, we cannot use any other types of milk that aren’t approved by KFT corporate as that deviates from the formulas they give us. We hope you’ll understand and give us another try in the future!

reviews_data.review_text:
Beware:  You only get the “happy hour” price IF you download their app, add your credit card (this prepaying), and order your tea.

THEN you’ll get an email stating “ VISIT: Receive a Free Drink (up to $5) on your third visit when using the app!”

So you will get a free drink upon your THIRD visit!

Lacking in customer service … when my son accidentally applied double my credit card purchase so I asked the manager, she said to contact Kung Fu Tea corporate- there was nothing she could do.  Really?? Can’t help?!

Disappointed.  Being new in town, Kung Fu Tea should know it’s about a good product and CUSTOMER EXPERIENCE.  I can’t judge the tea alone without seeing that I had a problem and wasn’t helped so well.  Could’ve been better.
The tea bubble tea was fine. A bit too sweet but that’s just personal preference.

Go to J Tea Tega Cay a mile down the road in the shopping center where Planet Fitness is for a better bubble tea experience and feel good that you are supporting a “Mom & Pop “ business.  And J Tea Tega Cay also offers yummy Vietnamese sandwiches for about $5.

J Tea Tega Cay:
921 Crossroads Plaza, Unit 30, Fort Mill, SC
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi there, Rose. We’re sorry you were less than satisfied with your experience today, and we appreciate you sharing your feedback. Kung Fu Tea is a franchise, and as such, there are so many things that are out of our control as a franchisee, like the products we put out or our menu prices. Another one of those things is the Kung Fu Tea app. Our store does not have any control over anyone’s app account, credit, or rewards. The eligibility for rewards and other app features are all done through corporate, so our manager to whom you spoke was correct in saying there was nothing we could do to help. Corporate controls the way we operate, and our employees unfortunately cannot change this fact. Please also refrain from taking and posting photos of our underaged employees without their consent. Thank you!

J Tea Tega Cay:
921 Crossroads Plaza, Unit 30, Fort Mill, SC
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi there, Rose. We’re sorry you were less than satisfied with your experience today, and we appreciate you sharing your feedback. Kung Fu Tea is a franchise, and as such, there are so many things that are out of our control as a franchisee, like the products we put out or our menu prices. Another one of those things is the Kung Fu Tea app. Our store does not have any control over anyone’s app account, credit, or rewards. The eligibility for rewards and other app features are all done through corporate, so our manager to whom you spoke was correct in saying there was nothing we could do to help. Corporate controls the way we operate, and our employees unfortunately cannot change this fact. Please also refrain from taking and posting photos of our underaged employees without their consent. Thank you!
